      "updated_at": "2016-05-30 16:13:29 UTC",
      "body": "This is probably caused by some missing key in the test scope. I'm not too motivated to figure out the issue since I personally dislike this setting. It plays badly with text editors and IDEs. I'm tempted to remove the setting from the sbt plugin and ask users instead to paste this snippet into their build:\r\n\r\n```scala\r\n    lazy val reformatOnCompileSettings: Seq[Def.Setting[_]] = List(\r\n        compileInputs in (Compile, compile) <<=\r\n          (compileInputs in (Compile, compile)) dependsOn (scalafmt in Compile),\r\n        compileInputs in (Test, compile) <<=\r\n          (compileInputs in (Test, compile)) dependsOn (scalafmt in Test)\r\n    )\r\n```"
    },
